======================================================================
PART 9: F(T, x) at special points
======================================================================
F(T, x) = sum over Ham paths P of x^{asc(P)}
F(T, 1) = n! / n = (n-1)! ... wait, F(T,1) = H(T)
Actually F(T, x) = sum_k F_k * x^k where F_k = # Ham paths with k ascents

  --- n=4 ---
    H: range [1, 5], mod2=Counter({1: 64}), mod3=Counter({1: 24, 2: 24, 0: 16})
